# Multi-Topic Interview Prep Architecture

This is a fantastic strategy to cover all the bases for product-based company interviews. Instead of just sending local notes, we will use Gemini as a personalized technical writer to generate deep-dive study material with code snippets!

## The Architecture
Instead of writing multiple Python scripts that do the exact same thing, we can build **one powerful script** (`generate_study_note.py`) that accepts a "topic" as a command-line argument. Then, we just create new GitHub Action schedules to trigger that script with different topics.

We will keep your 10:30 AM Quiz and 11:00 AM Answer system completely untouched.

### 1. Upgrade the Existing "MCA Notes" Cron
*   **[MODIFY]** `daily_mailer.py`: I will upgrade your original 10:00 AM script. Now, it will flip a coin:
    *   *50% chance:* It sends one of your local markdown notes (like it does now).
    *   *50% chance:* It uses Gemini to write a highly detailed, brand-new study note on an advanced Machine Learning or Generative AI concept, complete with code snippets.

### 2. The New Java & System Design Crons
*   **[NEW]** `generate_study_note.py`: A new Python script dedicated to writing deep-dive interview notes based on whatever topic we pass to it.
*   **[NEW]** `.github/workflows/note_java.yml`: We will schedule this to run at **12:00 PM IST**. It will trigger the script with the topic: *"Java 8 to 21, JVM Internals, and Spring Boot Interview Concepts"*.
*   **[NEW]** `.github/workflows/note_system_design.yml`: We will schedule this to run at **1:00 PM IST**. It will trigger the script with the topic: *"Large Scale System Design for FAANG Interviews"*.

